name: Flourless Double Chocolate Chip Zucchini Muffins
author: A Day In the Kitchen
summary: A moist chocolaty muffin that's free of flour and refined sugar, but full of flavor and yumminess.
ingredients: 1 cup finely grated zucchini, excess moisture squeezed out
¼ cup bittersweet chocolate chips, or to taste
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
Line muffin cups with aluminum foil liners
Mix almond butter, banana, cocoa powder, ground flax seeds, honey, vanilla extract, and baking soda together in a bowl until batter is well blended; fold in zucchini and semisweet chocolate chips
Scoop batter into the prepared muffin cups
Top each with bittersweet chocolate chips
Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 25 minutes
Place muffins on a wire rack to cool
